'''Richard A. Gabriel''' is a [[historian]] and [[author]].<ref name="macmillan">{{cite web|url=http://us.macmillan.com/author/richardagabriel|title=Richard A. Gabriel &#124; Authors &#124; Macmillan|publisher=us.macmillan.com|accessdate=2015-11-15}}</ref>
He is a professor in the Department of History and War Studies at the [[Royal Military College of Canada]] and in the Department of Defence Studies at the [[Canadian Forces College]] in [[Toronto]].<ref name="nyjournalofbooks">{{cite web|url=http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/people/richard-gabriel|title=Richard A. Gabriel &#124; New York journal of books|publisher=nyjournalofbooks.com|accessdate=2015-11-15}}</ref>
He is the author of books including ''Scipio Africanus: Rome’s Greatest General'', ''Hannibal: The Military Biography of Rome’s Greatest Enemy'',<ref>{{cite journal|last=Fronda|first=Michael P.|title=Hannibal: The Military Biography of Rome's Greatest Enemy. By Richard A. Gabriel. (book review)|journal=The Historian|date=Spring 2013|volume=75|issue=1|pages=197–198|doi=10.1111/hisn.12004_59}}</ref> ''The Great Armies of Antiquity'',<ref>{{cite journal|last=Sheldon|first=R. M.|title=The Great Armies of Antiquity by Richard A. Gabriel (review)|journal=The International History Review|date=Jun 2004|volume=26|issue=2|pages=353–356}}</ref> ''Man and Wound in the Ancient World''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Olle|first=David|title=Man and Wound in the Ancient World: A History of Military Medicine from Sumer to the Fall of Constantinople (review)|journal=New York Journal of Books|date=November 30, 2011|url=http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/review/man-and-wound-ancient-world-history-military-medicine-sumer-fall-constantinople}}</ref> and ''Military Incompetence''.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Simon|first=J Kirby|title=Military Incompetence, by Richard A. Gabriel (review)|journal=Commentary|date=April 1986}}</ref>
