{{BLP self-published|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox Officeholder |name = Sergei Ignatov |honorific-suffix = |image = Sergei Ignatov.jpg |caption = |office = [[Ministry of Education, Youth and Science (Bulgaria)|Minister of education, youth and science]] |primeminister = [[Boyko Borisov]] |term_start = 19 November 2009 |term_end = 28 January 2013 |predecessor = [[Yordanka Fandakova]] <small>([[Ministry of Education, Youth and Science (Bulgaria)|minister of education and science]]) |successor = Stefan Vodenicharov |office1 = [[Ministry of Education, Youth and Science (Bulgaria)|Vice minister of education and science]] |term_start1 = August 2009 |term_end1 = 19 November 2009 |primeminister1 = [[Boyko Borisov]] |predecessor1 = |successor1 = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1960|8|6|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Vidin]], [[Bulgaria]] |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[Citizens for European Development of Bulgaria|GERB]] }}
'''Sergei Simeonov Ignatov'''<ref>Sergei Ignatov, ''[https://www.jstor.org/pss/3821863?cookieSet=1 Some Notes on the Story of the Shipwrecked Sailor]'', The Journal of Egyptian Archaeology, Vol. 80, (1994), pp. 195-198</ref> (in [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]: Сергей Симеонов Игнатов; born August 6, 1960) is a [[Bulgaria]]n [[Egyptologist]] and [[politician]], [[Ministry of Education, Youth and Science (Bulgaria)|minister of education, youth and science]] from November 2009 to 28 January 2013.
Ignatov was born in [[Vidin]], [[Bulgaria]] on 6 August 1960.<ref name="meys">[http://mon.bg/opencms/opencms/left_menu/ministry/direction/cv_sergey_ingnatov.html Biography {{bg icon}}] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130115035348/http://mon.bg/opencms/opencms/left_menu/ministry/direction/cv_sergey_ingnatov.html |date=2013-01-15 }}, MEYS</ref> He graduated with a degree in [[Egyptology]] from [[Leningrad State University]] in 1985 and later specialized in [[All Souls College]], [[Oxford]]. He was lecturer and later associated professor at the [[University of Sofia]] (1985–1996) and at [[New Bulgarian University]] (1994–2009), dean of the bachelor faculty (1998–2002) and chancellor of NBU (2002–2009).<ref name="meys"/> Sergei Ignatov is Rector of [[European Humanities University]] in [[Vilnus]], [[Lithuania]] (since 2018).<ref>http://en.ehu.lt/news/former-bulgarian-minister-of-education-prof-sergei-ignatov-appointed-rector-of-ehu/</ref>
