'''Seth Schwartz''' is an American historian and is the [[Lucius Littauer|Lucius N. Littauer]] Professor of Classical Jewish Civilization at [[Columbia University]].
Schwartz earned the B.A. from [[Yeshiva University]] in 1979, and the Ph.D. from [[Columbia University]] in 1985.<ref name="Faculty Page">{{cite web|title=Seth Schwartz (faculty page)|url=http://history.columbia.edu/faculty/Schwartz.html|website=Columbia.edu|publisher=Columbia University|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref>
==Books== *''The Ancient Jews from Alexander to Muhammad,'' Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2014 *''Were the Jews A Mediterranean Society: Reciprocity and Solidarity in Ancient Judaism,'' Princeton: Princeton University Press, 2010. *''Imperialism and Jewish Society, 200 BCE to 640 CE,'' Princeton: Princeton University Press, 2001. *''Josephus and Judaean Politics,'' Leiden: Brill, 1990. *With R. Bagnall, A. Cameron and K. Worp, ''Consuls of the Later Roman Empire,'' Atlanta: Scholars Press, 1987.
