== Notes == {{Cnote2 Begin|liststyle=upper-alpha}} {{Cnote2|A|Sources vary as to the exact timescale of the migration of Khoisan from Southern Africa. Nurse & Spear say "as long as twenty thousand years ago".<ref name=Nurse />}} {{Cnote2|B|The [[Bantu expansion]] from West Africa likely happened in several stages.<ref name=Harrison /> Sources vary as to the exact timescale of the arrival of Bantu people to East Africa. Nurse & Spear say from "twenty-five hundred years ago".<ref name=Nurse /> Ndembwike says 100–200 AD.<ref name=Ndembwike />}} {{Cnote2|C|Several durations are given by sources, including 38,<ref name=hernon /><ref name=Haws /> 40<ref name=Jacopetti /> and 45<ref name=Gordon /> minutes, but the 38 minute duration is the most often quoted. The variation is due to confusion over what actually constitutes the start and end of a war. Some sources take the start of the war as the order to open fire at 09:00 and some with the start of actual firing at 09:02. The end of the war is usually put at 09:40 when the last shots were fired and the palace flag struck, but some sources place it at 09:45. The logbooks of the British ships also suffer from this with ''St George'' indicating that cease-fire was called and Khalid entered the German consulate at 09:35, ''Thrush'' at 09:40, ''Racoon'' at 09:41 and ''Philomel'' and ''Sparrow'' at 09:45.<ref name=Patience />}} {{Cnote2|D|There is no exact figure for the number of deaths in the Maji Maji Rebellion. German officials at the time estimated 75,000.<ref name=Shillington1539 /> Most sources say over 200,000.<ref name=Shillington1539 /><ref name=Longford189 /><ref name=Gellately />}} {{Cnote2 End}}
